synchronize_xccl_stream does not take an argument, so we must not pretend it does.
Old C code faked a nonexistent argument, nccl_stream, which was actually a global variable
New stricted GCC 15 no longer accepts this, as it's probably undefined behaviour

author: micketeer@gmail.com
diff -ru c.orig/xccl/collective/osu_xccl_allgather.c c/xccl/collective/osu_xccl_allgather.c
--- c.orig/xccl/collective/osu_xccl_allgather.c	2026-06-03 21:00:04.821135145 +0200
+++ c/xccl/collective/osu_xccl_allgather.c	2026-06-03 21:01:04.539198981 +0200
@@ -107,7 +107,7 @@
             t_start = MPI_Wtime();
             NCCL_CHECK(omb_xccl_interface->ncclAllGather(
                 sendbuf, recvbuf, size, ncclChar, nccl_comm, nccl_stream));
-            omb_xccl_interface->synchronize_xccl_stream(nccl_stream);
+            omb_xccl_interface->synchronize_xccl_stream();
             t_stop = MPI_Wtime();
 
             if (i >= options.skip) {
